The Edo State office of the Independent National Election Commission (INEC) has disclosed that a total of 127,561 Permanent Voter Cards (PVCs) have been collected in the state in eight days. The Head, Voter Education Department of INEC, Edo office, Timidi Wariowei, disclosed this yesterday in Benin while speaking with Daily Trust on the ongoing collection of PVCs in the state. He said the PVCs were collected by prospective voters between January 9 and 15. He also said the PVCs collection would revert to the INEC offices in the local governments across the state from January 23 to January 29, being the last day for the collection. 